Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:47.73,teGAKI,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,0)\fscx48.75\fscy98\3c&H161D60&\3a&H00&\4c&HF47410&\4a&HFF&\pos(585.563,906)}Democratic Republic of Congo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.39,0:04:42.78,White font,,0,0,0,,Congo, the heart of Africa's wonderful landscapes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:47.22,White font,,0,0,0,,What kind of scary stories are told in this country?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.09,0:04:55.06,Muwete,,0,0,0,,In a certain village in Congo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.12,0:04:58.86,Muwete,,0,0,0,,There was a young man called Pier Thunkai
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.12,0:05:02.50,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\4c&H000000&\4a&HFF&\fs37.5\pos(565.313,54)\fscx72.75\fscy133}note: I don't know its actual transcription. It's "pieerutuukai" in katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.67,0:07:37.86,teGAKI,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,500)\fscx38.25\fscy100\3c&H000000&\4c&HF47410&\4a&HFF&\pos(259.875,948)}Pier{\fs30} {\fs60}Thunkai
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:03.67,Muwete,,0,0,0,,One day, this young man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.67,0:05:05.67,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Wasn't home all day
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.59,0:05:10.51,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And while he was away
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.51,0:05:13.91,Muwete,,0,0,0,,All of his property were stolen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.61,0:05:19.71,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And so he started asking the villagers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:25.03,Muwete,,0,0,0,,"Who stole all the things I had?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:27.73,Muwete,,0,0,0,,While going around from house to house
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:32.49,Muwete,,0,0,0,,None of the villagers listened to him, though
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:36.13,Muwete,,0,0,0,,But unluckily for him
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.13,0:05:38.93,Muwete,,0,0,0,,At that moment, Pier Thunkai
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.07,0:05:40.85,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Accidentally slipped
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.85,0:05:43.71,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And fell down from a cliff
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.85,0:05:45.38,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\4c&H000000&\4a&HFF&\fs37.5\pos(565.313,54)\fscx72.75\fscy133}note: he mistakenly says "date" instead of "gake" (cliff)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.81,0:05:49.81,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And so, Pier Thunkai went missing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:54.22,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Later on, when it was night
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.22,0:05:58.75,Muwete,,0,0,0,,A monster showed up in the village
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:02.59,Muwete,,0,0,0,,That monster had a single eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.59,0:06:04.44,Muwete,,0,0,0,,A single leg,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.44,0:06:05.83,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And a single hand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.83,0:06:08.53,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Every single part of his body
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:10.87,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Was only one of a pair
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:15.40,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And so, that monster
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.40,0:06:18.01,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Started asking the villagers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.01,0:06:21.81,Muwete,,0,0,0,,"Where are all the things I had?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.34,0:06:25.71,Muwete,,0,0,0,,He started going from house to house
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:28.72,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Killing every villager he met
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:35.12,Muwete,,0,0,0,,The villagers shouted "please, don't kill anybody else!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.82,0:06:42.53,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And they started to chant \Na prayer to calm Pier Thunkai's anger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:44.63,Muwete,,0,0,0,,That song was like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:06:56.94,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And it repeats
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:12.86,Muwete,,0,0,0,,But that song didn't reach him at all
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:18.30,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Pier Thunkai just kept on killing each villager
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.30,0:07:22.44,Muwete,,0,0,0,,Until there was none of them left
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.81,0:07:26.04,Muwete,,0,0,0,,In Congo, to this day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:33.18,Muwete,,0,0,0,,We say "if you steal, Pier Thunkai will come for you!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.15,0:07:36.68,Muwete,,0,0,0,,And it came to be a common phrase
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:42.89,Hamada,,0,0,0,,What kind of story is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:45.79,Housei,,0,0,0,,It's Pier Thunkai's story
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.79,0:07:49.26,Hamada,,0,0,0,,How are Pier Thunkai and the halved monster related?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.26,0:07:50.07,Endo,,0,0,0,,It's the same
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.07,0:07:51.97,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Pier Thunkai himself became the monster
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.97,0:07:54.27,Hamada,,0,0,0,,He did?      {\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&HC23FAA&}- He transformed into the monster
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.74,0:07:56.27,Hamada,,0,0,0,,It came out so suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.27,0:07:57.41,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Yeah it was sudden
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.41,0:08:01.24,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,But almost everyone of us got that, \Nlike Cocorico and Yamazaki-san
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.24,0:08:02.98,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Yeah we did       {\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H079D12&}- I got that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.98,0:08:04.44,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Me too halfway
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.44,0:08:07.32,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd better off stop following it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:10.49,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,I mean, I can't even remember\N the main character's name
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.92,0:08:13.21,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Pier Thunkai, right?       {\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H1F9168&} - Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:15.39,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,So, he fell down a cliff\N{\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H1F9168&}- Yeah, he fell down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:16.66,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,And revived as a monster
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.66,0:08:19.07,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,He didn't fell down a cliff (gake)    {\3c&HC23FAA&}  {\c&HC23FAA&\3c&HFFFFFF&}- Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.07,0:08:20.90,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,He fell down a gliff (date)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.90,0:08:22.60,Endo,,0,0,0,,Of course he meant "cliff"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:23.73,Tanaka,,0,0,0,,Come on, get it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.30,0:08:28.00,White font,,0,0,0,,Next up is a scary story from Brazil
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:35.00,White font,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,200)\fs105\4c&H000000&\4a&HFF&\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H3F3B3C&\pos(455.625,1017)}M{\fs63\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H000000&}arzia
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.78,0:08:40.18,White font,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,100)\fs105\4c&H000000&\4a&HFF&\c&H22F2FA&\3c&H3F3B3C&\pos(455.625,1017)}M{\fs63\3c&H000000&\c&H22F2FA&}arzia
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:40.18,White font,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)\fscx36\fscy75\pos(609.188,873)}Brazil representative
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.94,0:08:38.48,Hamada,,0,0,0,,So, our representative for Brazil is miss Marzia
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.48,0:08:40.85,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you       {\3c&HFFFFFF&\c&H00C0FF&}- Same here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.85,0:08:42.12,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It's a ple{\c&H007FFF&}asure
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.75,0:08:44.12,Hamada,,0,0,0,,Whenever you're ready
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.25,0:08:52.59,Marzia,,0,0,0,,The story I'm about to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.59,0:08:57.23,Marzia,,0,0,0,,Is about an experience I really had \Nin Brazil when I was 14 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.87,0:09:00.00,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I was still very young
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:03.87,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And I was trying to call \Nfor a ghost, just for fun
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.17,0:09:09.88,Marzia,,0,0,0,,In short, I was doing something \Nlike the japanese "kokkuri-san"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.17,0:09:09.88,notes,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\4c&H000000&\4a&HFF&\fs37.5\pos(565.313,54)\fscx72.75\fscy133}note: a divination game similar to the western ouija board
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.80,0:09:14.35,Marzia,,0,0,0,,On the table, I've placed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.35,0:09:17.75,Marzia,,0,0,0,,Two cards labeled with "no" and "yes"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.08,0:11:25.96,teGAKI,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,0)\fscx38.25\fscy100\3c&H000000&\4c&HF47410&\4a&HFF&\pos(244.688,948)}The{\fs30} {\fs60}summoned{\fs30} {\fs60}spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.05,0:09:20.49,Marzia,,0,0,0,,Then I've light up two candles
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.49,0:09:24.33,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And planned to ask the ghost some questions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.33,0:09:26.09,Marzia,,0,0,0,,So it would answer, that's it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:29.53,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And so, I started the ritual
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:31.83,Marzia,,0,0,0,,But then suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.04,0:09:35.84,Marzia,,0,0,0,,The wind started to blow
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.84,0:09:38.81,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And when I opened my eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.81,0:09:39.87,Marzia,,0,0,0,,Before me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.47,0:09:43.68,Marzia,,0,0,0,,There was a blond kid
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.51,0:09:46.81,Marzia,,0,0,0,,So I asked him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.91,0:09:49.95,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"Who are you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.25,0:09:52.72,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And he said
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.72,0:09:55.09,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"I'm Paolo"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.09,0:09:57.66,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"I died in an accident"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.66,0:10:01.06,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"And I don't have any friends, \N so why don't you play with me?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.36,0:10:06.60,Marzia,,0,0,0,,That was the first time I saw \Na real ghost right before me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.99,0:10:10.04,Marzia,,0,0,0,,So I got really scared
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.14,0:10:13.84,Marzia,,0,0,0,,So I told Paolo
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.78,0:10:16.74,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"You're not in this world anymore"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.65,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"You shouldn't be here" - I desperately told him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.95,0:10:25.45,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And so he
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:29.95,Marzia,,0,0,0,,Quietly pointed his index towards the "no" card
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:33.83,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I gradually became even more terrified
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:36.13,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And, scared, I told him "go home"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:38.13,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"Please, just go back home!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.53,0:10:40.84,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And yet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.84,0:10:44.14,Marzia,,0,0,0,,He just kept on pointing the "no" card
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.61,0:10:47.74,Marzia,,0,0,0,,So i took the cards and the candles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.74,0:10:49.74,Marzia,,0,0,0,,On the table and took them away
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.10,0:10:52.58,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And cleaned everything up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.58,0:10:55.78,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And while shutting both my eyes and ears
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.25,0:11:00.96,Marzia,,0,0,0,,"Go away! Go Away! Vá embora! Vá embora!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.96,0:11:02.56,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I just kept on shouting this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.80,0:11:05.59,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And after some time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.59,0:11:08.00,Marzia,,0,0,0,,He disappeared into thin air
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.40,0:11:11.10,Marzia,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.33,0:11:16.34,Marzia,,0,0,0,,On the table, there was a single tarot card left
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.81,0:11:19.97,Marzia,,0,0,0,,When I looked at that tarot card...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.64,0:11:22.41,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I realized its meaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.99,0:11:25.15,Marzia,,0,0,0,,...was "friendship"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.15,0:11:34.02,Endo,,0,0,0,,Paolo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.20,0:11:36.76,Hamada,,0,0,0,,So, you actually experienced this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:39.12,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I was around 14 years old      {\c&HBB1906&}- 14 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.12,0:11:43.84,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I've always been kind of sensitive to ghost sighting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:46.20,Marzia,,0,0,0,,They're always sticking close to me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.20,0:11:48.29,Marzia,,0,0,0,,And always pop out, like, a lot of them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.29,0:11:50.78,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,So there's a chance it could stick close to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.78,0:11:52.54,Marzia,,0,0,0,,It could happen, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.54,0:11:53.41,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,Will it be Paolo?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.41,0:11:56.04,Marzia,,0,0,0,,If you call him, he may come but---
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.04,0:11:57.51,Marzia,,0,0,0,,Even tigers could come
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:11:58.18,Hamada,,0,0,0,,A tiger?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.18,0:12:02.15,Marzia,,0,0,0,,It actually happened I was once possessed by a tiger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.15,0:12:03.45,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.45,0:12:05.45,Marzia,,0,0,0,,It's not something to laugh about!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:08.35,Marzia,,0,0,0,,I'm not trying to sound funny
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:10.89,Marzia,,0,0,0,,This too was from that time, \NI was like 15 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.89,0:12:12.06,Housei,,0,0,0,,And what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.06,0:12:12.63,Marzia,,0,0,0,,A tiger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.63,0:12:14.20,Housei,,0,0,0,,And what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:15.66,Marzia,,0,0,0,,It bit me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:17.50,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It bit you?      {\c&H00C0FF&}- It did
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.50,0:12:19.33,Housei,,0,0,0,,It bit you?     {\c&H00C0FF&} - Yes, on the neck
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:21.07,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,It's scary, huhh
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.07,0:12:22.00,Marzia,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:25.92,Matsumoto,,0,0,0,,But it would be scary even if it wasn't a ghost
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:25.80,Marzia,,0,0,0,,{\pos(536.625,936)}No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:30.75,Housei,,0,0,0,,I mean, even if a non-ghost tiger would bite you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:36.35,White font,,0,0,0,,Next up for the World Scary Stories Summit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:39.49,White font,,0,0,0,,It's a story from our italian dandy
